==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forty
<hw>For"ty</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocir⟧r"t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>forti</ets>, <ets>fourti</ets>, <ets>fowerti</ets>, AS.
<ets>fe⟦oacute⟧wertig</ets>; <ets>fe⟦oacute⟧wer</ets> four + suff.
<ets>-tig</ets> ten; akin to OS. <ets>fiwartig</ets>,
<ets>fiartig</ets>, D. <ets>veertig</ets>, G. <ets>vierzig</ets>, Icel.
<ets>fj⟦oum⟧rut⟦imac⟧u</ets>, Sw. <ets>fyratio</ets>, Dan.
<ets>fyrretyve</ets>, Goth. <ets>fidw⟦omac⟧r tigjus</ets>. See
<er>Four</er>, and <er>Ten</er>, and cf. <er>Fourteen</er>.]</ety>
<def>Four times ten; thirty-nine and one more.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forty
<hw>For"ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Forties</plw>
<pr>(-t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The sum of four tens; forty
units or objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol expressing forty units; as, 40, or
xl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forty-niner</ent>⟦br⟧
